Class ITwoStateActuator<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.lakemonsters2635.actuator.interfaces.ITwoStateActuator<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - 

    public abstract class ITwoStateActuator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
    An actuator that is programmatically pushed forward and backwards. Implementation examples include:

    A piston that locks itself one way, and must be unlocked to go the other way
    A motor that must switch into a forward or reverse gear when going forwards or backwards
    A simple car.
    Author:
    Tristan
